PHASE 6: User Interface Development 


1Ô∏è‚É£ Lightning App Builder

Purpose: Build custom user interfaces without coding.

What to Do:

Navigate to Setup ‚Üí Lightning App Builder.

Create Custom Pages for different user groups (Procurement Officer, Project Manager, Director).

Add components like Related Lists, Tabs, Reports, and LWCs.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Record Pages

Purpose: Customize how records (Tender, Bid, Contract, Payment) appear.

Steps:

Go to Object Manager ‚Üí Tender ‚Üí Lightning Record Pages.

Add Highlights Panel, Tabs (Details, Related, Notes).

Insert Custom LWCs (like Tender Summary).

3Ô∏è‚É£ Tabs

Purpose: Provide quick navigation for custom objects.

Steps:

Setup ‚Üí Tabs ‚Üí New Custom Object Tab.

Add Tabs for Tender, Bid, Contract, Payment.

Assign to App Navigation.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Home Page Layouts

Purpose: Customize the Salesforce Home page.

Steps:

Setup ‚Üí Lightning App Builder ‚Üí Home Page.

Add:

Reports/Charts 

Tasks List.

Approvals Pending.

Custom Notifications panel.

5Ô∏è‚É£ Utility Bar

Purpose: Provide quick access to tools at the bottom of the screen.

Examples:

Add Notes.

Add Recent Items.

Add Custom LWC (e.g., Quick Tender Search).

6Ô∏è‚É£ Lightning Web Components (LWC)

Purpose: Build custom UI with JavaScript, HTML, and Apex integration.

Examples for Tender App:

Tender Summary Component ‚Üí Displays all bids and total amount.

Bid Submission Form ‚Üí Allows users to enter and submit a bid.

Contract Dashboard ‚Üí Shows contract progress and payments.

7Ô∏è‚É£ Apex with LWC

Purpose: Fetch Salesforce data via Apex into LWCs.


8Ô∏è‚É£ Events in LWC

Purpose: Communicate between components.

Types:

Child ‚Üí Parent (CustomEvent).

Parent ‚Üí Child (Public Property).

9Ô∏è‚É£ Wire Adapters

Purpose: Fetch data declaratively without writing Apex.


üîü Imperative Apex Calls

Purpose: Fetch or update data programmatically when an action happens.


